Provenance and modification notice (GPL-3.0 Section 5(a))
---------------------------------------------------------

This repository is a derivative work based on the Holocene Reconstruction
code:

    Upstream project: Holocene-Reconstruction/Holocene-code
    Source:           https://github.com/Holocene-Reconstruction/Holocene-code
    License:          GNU General Public License v3.0

The upstream code implements the offline paleoclimate data assimilation method
of Erb et al. (2022). Copyright in the original code remains with its
respective authors.

This template was modified and extended by David Edge, with contributions from
Nicholas McKay, Michael Erb, Julien Emile-Geay, and Deborah Khider, beginning
in 2026, to package the reconstruction as a reproducible, customizable template
driven by PReSto (Paleoclimate Reconstruction Storehouse). A summary of
modifications is maintained in CHANGELOG.md; the complete change record is the
Git commit history of this repository.

    Upstream version this template is based on:
        commit: dce870bb446a1436ea1246e19334671657fc16f7 (main)
        date:   2023-03-24

How to cite
-----------

If you use this software, please cite it using the metadata in CITATION.cff.
Please also cite the underlying method paper:

    Erb, M., McKay, N., Steiger, N., Dee, S., Hancock, C., Ivanovic, R.,
    Gregoire, L., and Valdes, P. (2022). Reconstructing Holocene temperatures
    in time and space using paleoclimate data assimilation. Climate of the
    Past, 18(12), 2599-2629. https://doi.org/10.5194/cp-18-2599-2022

